In its September 17 issue, Le Devoir published a letter from Mr. Patrick J. Garver, vice president and director of Canadian miner Barrick Gold.
Following an Orwellian logic, Barrick Gold claims that the world's largest gold company tried a six million euro defamation suit against three authors and a small publishing house in order to provoke a "transparent public debate".
If it is true that judges are independent and impartial, it is not the truth they judge, especially in the case of prosecutions for defamation, but the law.
