Why, according to Barrick Gold, would the best way to conduct a public debate be to harm anyone who dares to hold a position contrary to his own?
The outcome of the case is of little importance, the authors and the publisher of Noir Canada will have to spend considerable sums in order to prepare their defence and fight, with very unequal weapons, against an army of lawyers supported by the almost bottomless pockets of the miner.
